Niki de Saint Phalle - Wikipedia






















 






Niki de Saint Phalle

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search



Niki de Saint Phalle



1970 portrait by Lothar Wolleh



Born
Catherine-Marie-Agnès Fal de Saint Phalle
(1930-10-29)29 October 1930
Neuilly-sur-Seine, Hauts-de-Seine, France


Died
21 May 2002(2002-05-21) (aged 71)
La Jolla, California, United States


Nationality
French, American, (Swiss)


Education
Self-taught in art[1]


Known for
Sculpture, painting, filmmaking


Notable work
Nanas
Tarot Garden


Style
Nouveau réalisme, Feminist art


Spouse(s)
