 Niki De Saint Phalle
(1930–2002)


 
Writer |
 
Production Designer |
 
Director






Niki De Saint Phalle was born on October 29, 1930 in Neuilly-sur-Seine, France as Catherine Marie-Agnes Fal de Saint Phalle. She was a writer and production designer, known for Daddy (1973), Niki de Saint Phalle (1996) and Un rêve plus long que la nuit (1976). She was married to Jean Tinguely and Harry Mathews. She died on May 21, 2002 in ...            
See full bio »
            
 


